 1186","Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Skotland","Humbie, East Lothian, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Skotland","Scotland":"Skotland"},"nl":{"about 1166–1187":"circa 1166–1187","1166–1187":"1166–1187","1161–1225":"1161–1225","1187–1250":"1187–1250","1140–1220":"1140–1220","1147–Female":"1147–Overleden","1225":"1225","1147":"1147","1166":"1166","1187":"1187","1220":"1220","1140":"1140","1250":"1250","about 1187":"circa 1187","1161":"1161","about 1166":"circa 1166","about 1186":"circa 1186","Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Schotland","Humbie, East Lothian, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Schotland","Scotland":"Schotland"},"en":{"about 1166–1187":"about 1166–1187","1166–1187":"1166–1187","1161–1225":"1161–1225","1187–1250":"1187–1250","1140–1220":"1140–1220","1147–Female":"1147–Deceased","1225":"1225","1147":"1147","1166":"1166","1187":"1187","1220":"1220","1140":"1140","1250":"1250","about 1187":"about 1187","1161":"1161","about 1166":"about 1166","about 1186":"about 1186","Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Humbie, East Lothian, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Lorens","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Luis, Rafael, Jesus, Juan, Manuel, Alberto, Beatriz, Carlos, Miguel, Ramon, Rodrigo.","Catalan:","habitational name from any of the places called Lloréns in the provinces of Tarragona and Lleida."],"variants":[{"name":"Lawrence","meanings":["English: from the Middle English and Old French personal name <i>Lorens</i>, <i>Laurence</i>, from Latin <i>Laurentius</i> ‘man from <i>Laurentum</i>’, a place in Italy probably named from its laurels or bay trees. The name was borne by a Christian saint who was martyred at Rome in the 3rd century  AD ; he enjoyed a considerable cult throughout Europe, with consequent popularity of the personal name (French <i>Laurent</i>, Italian, Spanish <i>Lorenzo</i>, Catalan <i>Llorenç</i>, Portuguese <i>Lourenço</i>, German <i>Laurenz</i>, Polish <i>Wawrzyniec</i>, etc.). In Britain this is a common name from the 12th century, with pet forms such as   Law  ,   Low  ,   Lawrie  ,   Laurie  ,   Larry  ,   Larkin  , all of which are represented in surnames. There was also a feminine form <i>Laurencia</i> which may have given rise to the English surname. The surname is also borne by Jews among whom it is presumably an Americanized form of one or more similar (like-sounding) Ashkenazic surnames. In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed many cognates from other languages, e.g. German   Lorenz  , and also their patronymics and other derivatives, e.g. Slovenian <b>Lavrenčič</b> and <b>Lovrenčič</b> (patronymics from <i>Lavrencij</i> and <i>Lovrenc</i>, equivalents of <i>Lawrence</i>), Polish   Wawrzyniak  . Compare   Larrance  ,   Laurence  ,   Lawerence  ,   Lieurance  , and   Lowrance  ."]}]},{"name":"Ida","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a Norman name, of Germanic origin, derived from <i>īd</i> ‘work’. This died out during the later Middle Ages. It was revived in the 19th century, influenced by its use in  Tennyson's  The Princess (  1847 ) for the central character, who devotes herself to the cause of women's rights and women's education in a thoroughly Victorian way. The name is also associated with Mount Ida in Crete, which was connected in classical times with the worship of Zeus, king of the gods, who was supposed to have been brought up in a cave on the mountainside. In the 1930s it became famous as the name of the film star  Ida Lupino  (  1914–1995 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ida Lorens was born about 1166, in Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland, her father, Hugh Lorens, was 28 and her mother, Eda Fraser, was 20. She married Philip de Keith about 1186, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1187, in Scotland, at the age of 22."},"et":{"about 1166–1187":"umbes 1166–1187","1166–1187":"1166–1187","1161–1225":"1161–1225","1187–1250":"1187–1250","1140–1220":"1140–1220","1147–Female":"1147–Surnud","1225":"1225","1147":"1147","1166":"1166","1187":"1187","1220":"1220","1140":"1140","1250":"1250","about 1187":"umbes 1187","1161":"1161","about 1166":"umbes 1166","about 1186":"umbes 1186","Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Humbie, East Lothian, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1166–1187":"noin 1166–1187","1166–1187":"1166–1187","1161–1225":"1161–1225","1187–1250":"1187–1250","1140–1220":"1140–1220","1147–Female":"1147–Kuollut","1225":"1225","1147":"1147","1166":"1166","1187":"1187","1220":"1220","1140":"1140","1250":"1250","about 1187":"noin 1187","1161":"1161","about 1166":"noin 1166","about 1186":"noin 1186","Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Humbie, East Lothian, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1166–1187":"environ 1166–1187","1166–1187":"1166–1187","1161–1225":"1161–1225","1187–1250":"1187–1250","1140–1220":"1140–1220","1147–Female":"1147–Décédée","1225":"1225","1147":"1147","1166":"1166","1187":"1187","1220":"1220","1140":"1140","1250":"1250","about 1187":"environ 1187","1161":"1161","about 1166":"environ 1166","about 1186":"environ 1186","Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Écosse","Humbie, East Lothian, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Ida Lorens est née environ 1166, à Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Écosse, son père, Hugh Lorens, avait 28 ans et sa mère, Eda Fraser, avait 20 ans. Elle a épousé Philip de Keith environ 1186, à Écosse. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée en 1187,